                  <foliation/>
                  <collation>
                    <p>The quires were originally 15 in number and are signed with both letters and arithmetical figures (e.g. fol. <locus from="16">16</locus>,<foreign xml:lang="syr">ܓ</foreign>; fol. <locus from="28">28</locus>, <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܘ</foreign> ;  etc.)</p> <!-- Missing Arabic numbers! -->
                  </collation>
                  <condition>
                    <list>
                      <item>
                        <p>A few of the leaves are slightly stained and torn, especially foll. <locus from="1" to="3">1—3</locus>, <locus from="27">27</locus>, <locus from="54">54</locus>, <locus from="116">116</locus> and <locus from="118">118</locus>.</p>
                      </item>
                      <item>
                        <p>Of quires <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܕ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܗ</foreign> only two leaves remain, and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܒ</foreign> and <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܕ</foreign> are imperfect.</p>
                      </item>
                      <item>
                        <p>Leaves are wanting after foll. 9,15, 25, 26, 27, 38, and 44.</p>
                      </item>
                    </list>
                  </condition>
                </supportDesc>
                <layoutDesc>
                  <layout columns="1" writtenLines="24 28">
                    <locus from="" to=""/>
                    <p>There are from 24 to 28 lines in each page.</p>
                  </layout>
                </layoutDesc>
              </objectDesc>
              <handDesc hands="3">
                <handNote xml:id="handNote1" scope="major" script="syr-Syre" medium="unknown">
                  <desc>This volume is written in a fine, regular Estrangela of the vith cent.</desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote2" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition1">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
                <handNote xml:id="handNote3" scope="minor" script="syr" medium="unknown">
                  <desc><ref target="#addition2">See additions.</ref></desc>
                </handNote>
              </handDesc>
              <decoDesc/>
              <additions>
                <p/>
                <list>
                  <item n="1" xml:id="addition1">
                    <ref target="#handNote2"/>
                    <p>At the beginning and end of the manuscript, foll. <locus from="1" to="2a">1,2a</locus>, and <locus from="118a">118a</locus>, a more recent hand has written a <foreign xml:lang="syr">ܨܠܘܬܐ ܕܣܘܒܥܐ</foreign>.</p>
                  </item>
                  <item n="2" xml:id="addition2">
                    <locus from="117b"/>
                    <ref target="#handNote3"></ref>
                    <p>On the same page there are two notes, certifying that this was one of the 250 volumes brought to the <placeName>convent of S. Mary Deipara</placeName> by the <persName>abbat Moses of Nisibis</persName>, <date when-custom="1243" datingMethod="Seleucid">A. Gr. 1243</date>, <date when="0932" calendar="Gregorian">A.D. 932</date>.</p>
                    <p><quote xml:lang="syr">ܙܒܢ ܠܦܢܩܝܬܐ ܗܕܐ ܡܘܫܐ ܚܛܝܐ ܪܝܫܕܝܪܐ ܕܣܘܪ̈ܝܝܐ ܕܒܡܕܒܪܐ ܕܐܣܩ̈ܝܛܐ ܠܗ̇ ܠܕܝܪܐ. ܏ܘܫ.</quote></p>
                  </item>
                </list>
              </additions><!-- IF <additions> IS NOT USED, delete nested elements and make it an empty element.-->
